<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Moderate1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Moderate,</orth> adj. temperate, not excessive, holding the mean: <cit><quote>O love, be m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 112</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>m. lamentation,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>on a m. pace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 2, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>be m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a m. table,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.4.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 4, 117</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with m. haste,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.238" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 238</bibl></cit>.
